ts.append(index)\n            # Insert the number into the sorted list\n            sorted_nums.insert(index, num)\n        \n        # The counts are collected in reverse order, so reverse them back\n        return counts[::-1]\n```\n\nThis solution uses a binary search approach with a sorted list to efficiently determine the number of smaller elements to the right of each element in the input list. The `bisect_left` function is used to find the insertion point for each element in the sorted list, which corresponds to the count of smaller elements to its right. The sorted list is built in reverse order to facilitate this process.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}